{"title_page": "Cinema Foundation of Russia", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox company |\n| name = Fund Cinema Russia \n| logo =logo_FK.png\n| type = State-run film distributor, [[production company]]\n| foundation = 1994\n| location_city = Moscow \n| location_country = Russia \n| key_people = [[Leonid Vereshchagin]], [[Nikita Mikhalkov]], [[Timur Bekmambetov]], [[Feodor Bondarchuk]], Ruben Dishdishyan, Anton Malyshev \n| industry = [[Cinema of Russia|Russian cinema]]\n| products = film\n| num_employees = \n| revenue = \n| homepage = [http://www.fond-kino.ru Fond-Kino.ru/]\n}}\n\n'''Russian Cinema Fund Analytics''', known as '''Cinema Fund''' (\u0424\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u041a\u0438\u043d\u043e; Officially '''Federal Fund for Economic and social support of the Russian Cinematography''', \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0444\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438 \u044d\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u0438\u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0438), is the [[Government of Russia|Russian Government]]'s key funding body for the Russian screen production industry. Its functions are to support and promote the development of a highly creative, innovative and commercially sustainable industry, with a mandate to promote the creation and distribution of films in Russia as well as to preserve the country's film history.\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Cinema Foundation \u2013 About|url=http://www.fond-kino.ru/fund/|website=Cinema Fund|publisher=Fond Kino|accessdate=July 11, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705215553/http://www.fond-kino.ru/fund/|archive-date=July 5, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIt also had a production arm responsible for production and commissioning of films for the Russian Government. It was established by the [[Government of Russia]] in 1994 in order to promote the [[Cinema of Russia]] which celebrated 100th Birthday. The fund is considered as one of the most important federal regulators in the film industry in the Russian Federation.<ref>{{cite web|title=Russian Cinema Fund to provide support, not financing|url=http://m.rbth.co.uk/articles/2012/11/28/russian_cinema_fund_to_provide_support_not_financing_20481.html|website=Russia Behind The Headlines|publisher=RBTH|accessdate=July 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Background ==\nThe Foundation is financially assisting film and television production and also produced films generally intended for government purposes.\n\nAcross its various departments, The Fund supports the development, production, promotion and distribution of [[Cinema of Russia|Russian screen content]]. In 2015, the cinema fund decided to distribute among Russian filmmakers $43&nbsp;million (3&nbsp;billion rubles). In light of the ruble's sharp devaluation over the last months of 2014, the dollar figure is almost one half of what it was a year ago, when the 2014 budget was announced. Given the fact that many production expenses, including cast and crew fees, are nominated in U.S. dollars, local filmmakers received considerably less cash in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Russia's Cinema Fund Announces 2015 Budget|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/russias-cinema-fund-announces-2015-763278|website=Hollywood Reporter|publisher=Vladimir Kozlov|accessdate=July 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Pitch event==\nThe foundation is known for the [[Pitch (filmmaking)|Pitch]] Event that they are conduct every year in mid-April or March to allow the Russian film studios ask for financing their projects. This Pitch Events known as first glimpses to future Russian biggest cinema projects.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Roskino]]\n*[[Mosfilm]]\n*[[Lenfilm]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://eng.fond-kino.ru}}\n* {{imdb company|0405709}}\n\n[[Category:State-owned film companies]]\n[[Category:Film production companies of Russia]]\n[[Category:Film commissions]]\n[[Category:Documentary film organizations]]\n[[Category:Government agencies established in 1994]]\n[[Category:1994 establishments in Russia]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Moscow]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{Infobox company |\n| name = Russian Cinema Fund Analytics\n| logo =logo_FK.png\n| type = State-run film distributor, [[production company]]\n| foundation = 1994\n| location_city = Moscow \n| location_country = Russia \n| key_people = [[Leonid Vereshchagin]], [[Nikita Mikhalkov]], [[Timur Bekmambetov]], [[Feodor Bondarchuk]], Ruben Dishdishyan, Anton Malyshev \n| industry = [[Cinema of Russia|Russian cinema]]\n| products = film\n| num_employees = \n| revenue = \n| homepage = [http://www.fond-kino.ru Fond-Kino.ru/]\n}}\n\n'''Russian Cinema Fund Analytics''', known as '''Cinema Fund''' (\u0424\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u041a\u0438\u043d\u043e; Officially '''Federal Fund for Economic and social support of the Russian Cinematography''', \u0424\u0435\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0444\u043e\u043d\u0434 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0438 \u044d\u043a\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0439 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u0434\u0435\u0440\u0436\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442\u0435\u0447\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043a\u0438\u043d\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0444\u0438\u0438), is the [[Government of Russia|Russian Government]]'s key funding body for the Russian screen production industry. Its functions are to support and promote the development of a highly creative, innovative and commercially sustainable industry, with a mandate to promote the creation and distribution of films in Russia as well as to preserve the country's film history.\n<ref>{{cite web|